  "texts": [
    "AnsweringIn the answering step, accurate and contextually relevant answers to user queries are generated.",
    "This phase is essential for providing grounded responses based on the input query and the context extracted from relevant process model chunks retrieved in the previous phase, enhancing the overall effectiveness of the BPLLM pipeline.The answering stage requires two main components: a LLM and the corresponding tokenizer of the model.",
    "First, the prompt is crafted by combining the user query with the contextually relevant chunks retrieved in the previous phase as reported in Figure 4.",
    "The tokenizer has the task of preprocessing the prompt and converting it into a format that can be understood by the model.",
    "Tokenization involves breaking down the input text into individual tokens and encoding them into numerical representations that the model can process."
  ],
